nt" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>NIINIST&#xd6;</last-name><first-name>Jyrki</first-name><address><city>Halikko</city><country>FI</country></address></addressbook><residence><country>FI</country></residence></us-applicant></us-applicants><inventors><inventor sequence="00" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>APELL</last-name><first-name>Mika</first-name><address><city>Turku</city><country>FI</country></address></addressbook></inventor><inventor sequence="01" designation="us-only"><addressbook><last-name>NIINIST&#xd6;</last-name><first-name>Jyrki</first-name><address><city>Halikko</city><country>FI</country></address></addressbook></inventor></inventors></us-parties><assignees><assignee><addressbook><orgname>EVONDOS OY</orgname><role>03</role><address><city>Salo</city><country>FI</country></address></addressbook></assignee></assignees></us-bibliographic-data-application><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">Method, arrangement and apparatus for administrating dispensing medication in which the arrangement receives user information to authorize access of a user according to defined user roles to control patient care events. The arrangement receives care related information for the patient based on the user information defining the user role in the arrangement. A medication item to be taken by the patient is then detected and item information of at least one detected medication item is read. By comparing the item information with care related information the patient is authorized to receive the medication item. A reminder can be set to allow the patient to receive the medication item on a delivery time based on the care related and item information. Upon receiving the medication item on the delivery time, the actual delivery time together with item information is communicated to acknowledge the reminder.</p></abstract></us-patent-application>